data.database_description: This database is designed to manage maintenance contracts, assets, parts, and staff involved in asset management. It tracks third-party companies that provide services and supplies, engineers with their skills, fault logs for assets, and visits by engineers to resolve issues. The schema supports the detailed recording of maintenance activities, including the relationship between assets and parts, as well as the skills required to fix specific faults.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each company.
Type of the company (e.g., Maintenance Contractor, Supplier).
Name of the company.
Address of the company.
Additional details about the company.

sample_data: 1, Maintenance Contractor, Langworth-Funk, 615 Jacobs Mews, Uganda
2, Supplier, McDermott Group, 873 Conrad Creek Apt. 286, China
3, Maintenance Contractor, Schuppe-Carroll, 066 Bechtelar Ridge, United Arab Emirates
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about third-party companies including their type, name, address, and additional details.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each maintenance contract.
Identifier linking the maintenance contract to its company.
Start date of the maintenance contract.
End date of the maintenance contract.
Additional details about the maintenance contract.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about maintenance contracts including their company, start and end dates, and additional details.

columns.columnDescription: The unique identifier for a part.
The name of the part.
Indicates whether the part is chargeable (1) or not (0).
The amount charged for the part, if applicable.
Additional details about the part.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: This table contains information about the parts used in assets.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each skill.
Code representing the skill, typically a short acronym.
Detailed description of the skill.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about different skills required for maintenance activities.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each staff member.
Name of the staff member.
Gender of the staff member (1 for male, 0 for female).
Additional details about the staff member.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about staff members involved in asset management.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each asset.
Identifier linking the asset to its maintenance contract.
Identifier linking the asset to its supplier company.
Additional details about the asset.
Make or manufacturer of the asset.
Model number of the asset.
Date when the asset was acquired.
Date when the asset was disposed.
Other relevant details about the asset.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about assets including their maintenance contract, supplier, details, and disposal status.

columns.columnDescription: The unique identifier for an asset.
The unique identifier for a part.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: This table stores the relationship between assets and parts.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for an engineer (Primary Key).
Identifier for the third-party company the engineer works for.
First name of the engineer.
Last name of the engineer.
Additional details about the engineer.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about engineers involved in maintenance activities.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for an engineer.
Identifier for a specific skill possessed by the engineer.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores the skills of each engineer.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each fault log entry.
Identifier for the asset with the fault.
Identifier for the staff member who recorded the fault.
Timestamp when the fault was logged.
Description of the fault.
Additional details about the fault.
Unique identifier for each engineer visit.
Identifier for the staff member contacted during the visit.
Identifier for the engineer performing the visit.
Reference to the fault log entry associated with this visit.
Status of the fault at the end of the visit.
Start time of the engineer visit.
End time of the engineer visit.
Additional details about the visit.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records visits by engineers to resolve asset faults.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a part fault.
Identifier for the part associated with the fault.
Short name or code for the fault.
Detailed description of the fault.
Additional details about the fault, if any.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about faults associated with parts, including a short name, description, and additional details.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a fault log entry.
Unique identifier for a part fault.
Status of the fault, such as 'Reported', 'Return', or 'Fixed'.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records the relationship between fault log entries and parts, along with the status of each fault.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for a specific part fault.
Identifier for the skill required to fix the part fault.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Maps part faults to the skills required to fix them.
